Feature: after the centralized poll propagates a dependency release, the rebuilt bc-base:latest carries that released version

  Pins the end-to-end OUTCOME of the centralized rebuild path (ADR-022 D2):
  after a baked dependency releases a newer version, the published
  bc-base:latest installs that released version rather than the old hard-pinned
  one. This scenario survives ADR-022's supersession of the trigger mechanism —
  its end goal (the rebuilt :latest carries the released dependency version) is
  unchanged — but its MECHANISM prose is re-authored OFF the retired per-repo
  repository_dispatch fan-in and ONTO the ADR-022 centralized poll: the bump is
  what the scheduled workflow applies when it resolves a newer latest release
  ("bumps the @vMAJOR.MINOR.PATCH pin ... if the latest tag differs from the
  baked pin; if any pin changed, rebuilds bc-base and republishes :latest"), not
  a tag carried in a dispatch client_payload. The prior authoring
  (@scenario_hash edd2c813688ab768) described the dispatch-client_payload path
  and is SUPERSEDED by this re-authoring. Composes with scenario 59 (bump-then-
  rebuild) as its observable on the published image. (Targets
  shopsystem-bc-launcher.)

  @scenario_hash:69904daef7a8d13e
